HEADWORD: Kolushan
<hw>Ko*lush"an</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From Russ. <ets>kalyushka</ets> piece of wood (worn
in the nether lip).]</ety> <def>Designating, or pertaining to, a
linguistic stock of North American Indians comprising the Tlinkit tribes
of the Alexander Archipelago of southeastern Alaska and adjacent coast
lands. Their language bears some affinity to Mexican tongues.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

